Correct me if I'm wrong as I don't have much django experience.

Creation of related resources via the `relationships` key is unsupported. See http://jsonapi.org/format/upcoming/#crud-creating For example
```
{
  "data": {
    "type": "photos",
    "attributes": {
      "title": "Ember Hamster",
      "src": "http://example.com/images/productivity.png"
    },
    "relationships": {
      "photographer": {
        "data": { "type": "people", "id": "9" }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

this could be achieved by adding a `create` method on the serializers. See http://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/relations/#writable-nested-serializers in https://github.com/django-json-api/django-rest-framework-json-api/blob/develop/example/serializers.py

Please let me know if this would be a welcome feature and I will submit a PR.

